abstract: In the Perspective "alpha-Helical coiled coils: More facts and better predictions" by C. Cohen and D. A. D. Parry (28 Jan., p. 488), the second sentence of the second paragraph of column 1 on page 489 should have read, "The structural motif is indeed a left-handed three-helix bundle with left-handed chain connectivity."

29 April (p.734) and 13 May (p. 911) issues of Science The talk being given by Dr. Harold Varmus at the Science/HUGO Human Genome 1994 meeting on Monday, 3 October, in Washington, D.C., is entitled "Manipulating Cancer Genes in the Mouse."
